gomodel:SYNGO_4108  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Fig 1E: Co-immunostaining for PRRT2 and presynaptic protein SYP on brain slices indicated similar expression patterns.\nFig 1F-G: Post-embedding immunogold labelling for electron microscopy showed PRRT2 immunoreaction product in the presynaptic structures.\nFig 1H: Immunoblots of isolated fractions from mouse brain lysates show that PRRT2 does not exist in the postsynaptic density. SYP, SNAP25 and PSD95 were used as protein markers to validate different ultrasynaptic compartments.\nFigure S1: Literal:\nThe specificity of the antibodies was verified by western blotting with lysates from cultured mouse cortical neurons and the results indicate that the immunostained band at 65 kDa indeed represents the endogenous PRRT2.. Experimental description: The Prrt2Stop knock-in mutant mice were generated in a C57BL/6J background by CRISPR/Cas-mediated genome editing. The IHC, EM experiments were conducted in C57BL/6J mouse." ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-2916-7616" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" ;
        dc:date           "2021-01-18" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_4108" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .

